<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14295] FetchMessageConversionsPerSec meter not recorded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14295</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The broker topic metric FetchMessageConversionsPerSec doesn&apos;t get recorded on a fetch message conversion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug is that we pass in a callback that expects a MultiRecordsSend in KafkaApis:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
def updateConversionStats(send: Send): Unit = {
  send match {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; send: MultiRecordsSend &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; send.recordConversionStats != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; =&amp;gt;
      send.recordConversionStats.asScala.toMap.foreach {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; (tp, stats) =&amp;gt; updateRecordConversionStats(request, tp, stats)
      }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; _ =&amp;gt;
  }
} &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we call this callback with a NetworkSend in the SocketServer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
selector.completedSends.forEach { send =&amp;gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
    val response = inflightResponses.remove(send.destinationId).getOrElse {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IllegalStateException(s&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Send &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; ${send.destinationId} completed, but not in `inflightResponses`&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
    }
    updateRequestMetrics(response)

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Invoke send completion callback
&lt;/span&gt;    response.onComplete.foreach(onComplete =&amp;gt; onComplete(send))
...&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that Selector.completedSends returns a collection of NetworkSend&lt;/p&gt;</description>
